At late times the [cosmological term](universe curvature) dominates:

$a(t)\sim e^{\sqrt{\Lambda/3ct}}$

$H$ becomes a constant. As a result the *coordinate* speed of light becomes attenuated: $c/a(t)\sim ce^{-Ht}$. Even if we wait forever, the photon will not get to a place that is far enough.

